# RealEST Project Context for Zed AI Assistant

## Project Information
Project: RealEST - Vetted & Verified Property Marketplace
Domain: realest.ng
Target Market: Nigeria (primary), Africa (expansion)
Tech Stack: Next.js 16, React 19, HeroUI v3, UntitledUI, Tailwind CSS v4, Supabase

## Design System Context
Primary Context File: docs/zed-context-realest-design-system.md

## Brand Colors (OKLCH)
- Primary Dark: #07402F (oklch(0.30 0.06 165)) - 60% usage
- Primary Accent: #ADF434 (oklch(0.89 0.24 128)) - 10% usage
- Primary Neutral: #2E322E (oklch(0.26 0.01 155)) - 30% usage
- Brand Light: #F8F9F7 (oklch(0.98 0.005 155)) - Light backgrounds

## Typography
- Display: Lufga (hero sections)
- Heading: Neulis Neue (titles, headers)
- Body: Space Grotesk (content, forms)
- Mono: JetBrains Mono (data, coordinates)

## Component Strategy
- HeroUI v3: Primary components (70%) - buttons, cards, forms, navigation
- UntitledUI: Status/state components (25%) - badges, chips, alerts
- Shadcn/UI: Complex patterns only (5%) - data tables, specialized forms

## Available MCPs
- HeroUI MCP: Real-time HeroUI v3 documentation and examples
- Supabase MCP: Current Supabase patterns and implementation guides

## Key Principles
1. Nigerian market cultural sensitivity
2. Geotag verification focus
3. Trust-building UI patterns
4. Mobile-first responsive design
5. Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)
6. Performance optimization

## File Structure
- /components/ui/heroui - Customized HeroUI components
- /components/ui/untitledui - UntitledUI status components
- /components/property - Property-specific components
- /components/dashboard - Dashboard components
- /lib/supabase - Supabase client and utilities
- /styles/tokens - Design system tokens

## Development Guidelines
- Always reference design system context file
- Use MCP servers for component documentation
- Follow established spacing scale (4px base)
- Implement proper TypeScript types
- Ensure responsive design across all components
- Include loading and error states
- Follow brand voice: confident, supportive, Nigerian-aware

## Nigerian Property Context
- Support for States/LGAs
- Boys Quarters (BQ) accommodation
- Estate vs individual properties
- Security-focused messaging
- Infrastructure availability indicators
- Local transportation references

This context ensures Zed AI understands the project scope, design system, and cultural considerations for effective code assistance.
